    "Different methods can be used to implement these specified principles However, in any case, there must be specialized clinics of national importance that will coordinate the efforts of regional rehabilitation centers.",
    "The first possible way is to create rehabilitation centers within mental health services, which could make them more accessible to military personnel, since these facilities already exist and have the resources to provide care.",
    "Such centers may provide both medical and psychological services ensuring a comprehensive approach to rehabilitation.",
    "However, this path may become a subjective obstacle for service recipients due to the stigmatizing aspect of psychiatry.",
    "Unfortunately, the staff occupied at the centers of this type may be less competent in working with military personnel, which may affect the quality of service provision, and the facility itself may have limited resources and capabilities compared to other specialized centers."
